                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-214-off1214 t18291029-214-victim1770"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-214-person1771">
                  JAMES 
                  WATT
               <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1771" type="surname" value="WATT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1771" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1771" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner had a room on the same floor as me. On the 12th of September my wife was out nursing, and I had to make my own bed - I went out, and put the key under the mat in case my wife should come home; when I came home I saw the bed clothes pulled about, and missed the blanket - there is no mark on this, but I had a pair of them, and this is the same as the other.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-214-person1772">
                  CHARLES 
                  WILLIAMSON
               <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1772" type="surname" value="WILLIAMSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1772" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1772" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This blanket was pawned with me by the prisoner, on the 12th of September, about twelve or one o'clock.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. That man has sworn false - I came home, took my own blanket, and pawned it for 2s.; he has owed me a great animosity for some time, because I said he brought in women of a night.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-214-person1773">
                  JAMES 
                  WATT
               <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1773" type="surname" value="WATT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1773" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1773" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. Q. Did she complain of you for bringing women to the house? A. No; I never had any one there but my wife; I have lived with Mr. Burgin eleven years - the man she lives with is not her husband; she came up to me for a light when they came there, and I said to my wife, "I don't like these people, for I heard him beat her, and she threatened to hang him;" I never spoke to her but once in anger, when she was coming up- I told her to keep her distance; I am sure my blanket was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-214-person1774">
                  CHARLES 
                  WILLIAMSON
               <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1774" type="surname" value="WILLIAMSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1774" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-214-person1774" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. Q. Did she say before the Magistrate it was her own? A. Yes; she has not often pawned blankets, but I have known her these twenty years, and never knew any thing wrong of her.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18291029-214-verdict1216" type="verdictDescription">
